File: EFF Deputy President Floyd Shivambu. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The trial date of Floyd Shivambu has been postponed. The National Prosecuting Authority says that EFF deputy president’s defence has requested that the case be moved to 2 June. READ: Shivambu assault trial date expected in February Shivambu was expected to appear in the Cape Town magistrate's court on Thursday. He’s accused of common assault after allegedly attacking journalist Adrian de Kock. The altercation took place in March 2018 when Shivambu refused to have his picture taken at Parliament’s Precinct. READ: Shivambu appears in court over assault of journalist Both Shivambu and De Kock were unable to settle the matter out of court. No reasons have yet been given for the postponement.